## Subtask 2: moveCard with Fractional Indexing

### 2a. Write tests first (add to db.test.mjs)

#### Describe: `moveCard` (before: `initDb(':memory:')`, after: `closeDb()`)

Each test is self-contained (creates its own cards):
- `'moves card to empty column'` — create A in ready, `moveCard(A.id, 'done', 0)`, assert `column=done, position=1.0`
- `'moves card to first position in populated column'` — B,C in done; move A to index 0; assert A.position < B.position
- `'moves card to last position in populated column'` — B,C in done; move A to index 2; assert A.position > C.position
- `'moves card to middle of column'` — B,C,D in done; move A to index 1; assert B.position < A.position < C.position
- `'returned card reflects new column and position'` — assert `result.id, result.column, typeof result.position === 'number'`
- `'same-column move to later position'` — A,B,C in ready; move A to index 2; assert order B,A,C
- `'same-column move to earlier position'` — A,B,C in ready; move C to index 0; assert order C,A,B
- `'renormalizes when gap < 0.001'` — raw insert two cards with positions 1.000 and 1.0004; move third card to index 1; assert all positions become integers (1.0, 2.0, 3.0); assert relative order preserved
- `'throws NotFoundError for non-existent card'` — try/catch, assert `err instanceof NotFoundError`
- `'negative targetIndex treated as first position'` — `moveCard(A.id, 'done', -1)`, assert A.position < B.position
- `'large targetIndex treated as last position'` — `moveCard(A.id, 'done', 99)`, assert A.position > C.position

### 2b. Implementation: `moveCard` (add to queries.js)

**Algorithm** (integer targetIndex = 0-based desired rank among siblings):

```javascript
export function moveCard(id, column, targetIndex) {
  const card = stmts.getCardById.get(id);
  if (!card) throw new NotFoundError(`Card not found: ${id}`);

  const doMove = db.transaction(() => {
    const siblings = stmts.getSiblings.all(column, id);

    if (siblings.length === 0) {
      stmts.updateCardPos.run({ column, position: 1.0, id });
    } else if (targetIndex <= 0) {
      stmts.updateCardPos.run({ column, position: siblings[0].position / 2, id });
    } else if (targetIndex >= siblings.length) {
      stmts.updateCardPos.run({ column, position: siblings[siblings.length - 1].position + 1.0, id });
    } else {
      const before = siblings[targetIndex - 1].position;
      const after  = siblings[targetIndex].position;
      const gap    = after - before;

      if (gap >= 0.001) {
        stmts.updateCardPos.run({ column, position: (before + after) / 2, id });
      } else {
        // Renormalize: build new order with moved card spliced in
        const renorm = db.prepare('UPDATE cards SET "column" = ?, position = ? WHERE id = ?');
        const newOrder = [
          ...siblings.slice(0, targetIndex),
          { id },
          ...siblings.slice(targetIndex),
        ];
        newOrder.forEach((s, i) => renorm.run(column, i + 1.0, s.id));
      }
    }

    return stmts.getCardById.get(id);
  });

  return doMove();
}
```

**Key invariants**:
- `getSiblings` excludes the moved card (so same-column moves work without special casing)
- Renormalization loop handles all cards in the column, including the moved card
- `db.prepare()` inside transaction body is valid in better-sqlite3

