233	## Subtask 2: moveCard with Fractional Indexing
234	
235	### 2a. Write tests first (add to db.test.mjs)
236	
237	#### Describe: `moveCard` (before: `initDb(':memory:')`, after: `closeDb()`)
238	
239	Each test is self-contained (creates its own cards):
240	- `'moves card to empty column'` — create A in ready, `moveCard(A.id, 'done', 0)`, assert `column=done, position=1.0`
241	- `'moves card to first position in populated column'` — B,C in done; move A to index 0; assert A.position < B.position
242	- `'moves card to last position in populated column'` — B,C in done; move A to index 2; assert A.position > C.position
243	- `'moves card to middle of column'` — B,C,D in done; move A to index 1; assert B.position < A.position < C.position
244	- `'returned card reflects new column and position'` — assert `result.id, result.column, typeof result.position === 'number'`
245	- `'same-column move to later position'` — A,B,C in ready; move A to index 2; assert order B,A,C
246	- `'same-column move to earlier position'` — A,B,C in ready; move C to index 0; assert order C,A,B
247	- `'renormalizes when gap < 0.001'` — raw insert two cards with positions 1.000 and 1.0004; move third card to index 1; assert all positions become integers (1.0, 2.0, 3.0); assert relative order preserved
