337	## Subtask 4: Prepared Statements
338	
339	All queries are already prepared statements in the design above. The `updateCard` function cannot pre-prepare (dynamic SET clause), so it calls `db.prepare()` inline per call — this is intentional and safe (better-sqlite3 `prepare` is fast).
340	
341	No additional work needed beyond verifying the statement cache in `_prepareStatements()` covers all hot paths.
342	
343	---
344	
345	## Subtask 5: Error Handling
346	
347	### Error classes (in queries.js)
348	```javascript
349	export class NotFoundError extends Error { ... }     // card/comment not found
350	export class DatabaseError extends Error { ... }      // generic DB error
351	export class ForeignKeyError extends DatabaseError { ... }  // FK violation
352	```
